Advance Excel Assignment 4

Q1. To use the ribbon commands, what menu and grouping of commands will you find the Insert and Delete command?
Ans: To use the ribbon commands for Insert and Delete, you will find them under the "Home" menu tab, in the "Cells" grouping of commands.

Q2. If you set a row height or column width to 0 (zero), what happens to the row and column?
Ans: If you set a row height or column width to 0 (zero), the row or column will be hidden from view, effectively making it invisible on the worksheet.

Q3. Is there a need to change the height and width in a cell? Why?
Ans: There is no need to change the height and width in a cell unless you want to adjust the appearance or layout of the worksheet. Changing height and width can help optimize the presentation of data and make it more readable.

Q4. What is the keyboard shortcut to unhide rows?
Ans: The keyboard shortcut to unhide rows in Excel is Ctrl + Shift + 9.

Q5. How to hide rows containing blank cells?
Ans: To hide rows containing blank cells, select the rows you want to hide, right-click, choose "Hide" from the context menu, and the selected rows with blank cells will be hidden.

Q6. What are the steps to hide the duplicate values using conditional formatting in excel?
Ans: Steps to hide duplicate values using conditional formatting in Excel:
   - Select the range of cells containing the data.
   - Go to the "Home" tab on the ribbon.
   - Click on "Conditional Formatting" and choose "Highlight Cells Rules."
   - Select "Duplicate Values."
   - Choose formatting options for the duplicate values and click "OK."
